Our first female F-35 production and training pilot has taken to the skies for the first time in the #F35. Welcome to the F-35 family, “Siren," and thank you for setting an incredible example for aspiring female pilots around the world. 

Check out our story for more!

node.text:
On June 17, history was made. Our fifth GPS III satellite for the @spaceforcedod was the first national security mission to ride to space on a reused @spacex rocket.

The satellite took to the skies from sunny Cape Canaveral, with its sights set on its orbital home 12,550 miles above the Earth.
#rockets #rocketscience #rocketlaunch #GPS

Forty years ago, the F-117 Nighthawk, the world’s first stealth aircraft, soared through the skies on its maiden flight. 

Today, it is a lasting example of Skunk Works® innovation and rapid response to our nation’s mission-critical needs.

node.text:
Our Skunk Works® team is proving the value of digitally enabled aircraft development to design, build and deliver aircraft faster than ever before. 

Meet CHARLIE, a born-digital prototype of Project StarDrive that’s paving the way for the future of aircraft development. 

#SkunkWorks #engineering #aircraft #aerospace

node.text:
The GOES-T satellite completes solar array deployment testing at our Space facility just outside Denver, Colorado. 

The GOES-R satellite series improves weather forecasting quality and timeliness generating significant economic benefits to the nation in the areas of climate monitoring, ecosystems management, commerce and transportation.

node.text:
Right side up or upside down, the F-35 Demonstration Team puts on a show.
 
This team travels the world to showcase the capabilities of the #F35 and the professionalism of the men and women in the @usairforce. Follow @f35demoteam to stay in the loop!

node.text: Next month, a fleet of @ministryofdefence and @usmarinecorps F-35Bs will board @hmsqueenelizabeth as part of the Carrier Strike Group’s maiden deployment. The #CSG21 will participate in @nato exercises and maritime security operations in the Indo-Pacific region.
